President Obama expresses his condolences to the family of Senator James M. Jeffords, who passed away. He acknowledges Jeffords' dedication to public service throughout his life, as a naval officer, a local leader, and a U.S. Senator representing Vermont. Obama highlights Jeffords' independent spirit and his commitment to voting based on his principles, even if it meant taking unpopular positions. He commends Jeffords for his legacy of service and offers prayers to his family.